<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="364" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[113,1089,1121,1336]" pageId="13" pageNumber="364">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,224,1121,1144]" pageId="13" pageNumber="364">Remarks.</emphasis>
When I was assembling the data for my previous paper on 
<taxonomicName authority="(SEKERKA 2014)" baseAuthorityName="SEKERKA" baseAuthorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="364" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Imatidiini">
Imatidiini (
<bibRefCitation author="SEKERKA L." pageId="13" pageNumber="364" pagination="257 - 314" refId="ref20282" refString="SEKERKA L. 2014: Review of Imatidiini genera (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 54: 257 - 314." type="journal article" year="2014">SEKERKA 2014</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
I tentatively placed this species to 
<taxonomicName authority="Sekerka, 2014" authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2014" box="[564,861,1153,1176]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Windsorispa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="364" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[564,697,1153,1176]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="364">Windsorispa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="SEKERKA L." box="[707,861,1153,1176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="364" pagination="257 - 314" refId="ref20282" refString="SEKERKA L. 2014: Review of Imatidiini genera (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 54: 257 - 314." type="journal article" year="2014">Sekerka, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
because 
<bibRefCitation author="PIC M." box="[963,1089,1153,1176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="364" pagination="1 - 32" refId="ref20230" refString="PIC M. 1926 a: Nouveautes diverses. Melanges Exotico-Entomologiques 46: 1 - 32." type="journal article" year="1926">PIC (1926a)</bibRefCitation>
compared it to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Weise, 1910)" baseAuthorityName="Weise" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[270,544,1185,1208]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Windsorispa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="364" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifrons">
<emphasis box="[270,390,1185,1208]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="364">W. latifrons</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="WEISE J." box="[403,536,1185,1208]" pageId="13" pageNumber="364" pagination="67 - 127" refId="ref20925" refString="WEISE J. 1910: Beitrag zur Kenntnis der amerikanischen Hispinen. Archiv fur Naturgeschichte 76: 67 - 127." type="journal article" year="1910">Weise, 1910</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and the type was on loan to another researcher. Last year I had opportunity to study the 
<typeStatus box="[499,592,1217,1240]" pageId="13" pageNumber="364">holotype</typeStatus>
and found that it in fact belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Aslam, 1966" authorityName="Aslam" authorityYear="1966" box="[113,428,1249,1272]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Pseudimatidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="364" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[113,286,1249,1272]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="364">Pseudimatidium</emphasis>
Aslam, 1966
</taxonomicName>
and is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pic, 1936)" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1936" box="[674,908,1249,1272]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Pseudimatidium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="364" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="madoni">
<emphasis box="[674,780,1249,1272]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="364">P. madoni</emphasis>
(Pic, 1936)
</taxonomicName>
, which differs in stronger punctation of elytra and pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
